episodes.title: Episode 47: AgeProof! Living Longer Without Running Out Of Money Or Breaking A Hip
episodes.author: Jean Chatzky
episodes.summary: No matter how long you think you're going to live, chances are you're going to live longer. Especially if you're a woman. And since your health and financial life are critically intertwined, I joined forces with Dr. Michael Roizen of the Cleveland Clinic to literally write the book — out just this week — to help you AgeProof your life.

episodes.title: Episode 46: All You Need To Know About Sex And Money, But Were Afraid To Ask!
episodes.author: Jean Chatzky
episodes.summary: Money and sex. They're the two things couples fight about most and talk about least, so we're turning up the heat with love and relationships expert Dr. Pepper Schwartz.

episodes.title: Episode 45: No More Excuses
episodes.author: Jean Chatzky
episodes.summary: Investing isn't hard, but we know taking the first step can be. Did you know women are actually better investors than men, yet they tend to make more excuses for not starting?

episodes.title: Episode 44: Moneyball, The Dating Edition
episodes.author: Jean Chatzky
episodes.summary: Just in time for Valentine's Day... If you, your adult kids or your friends are single and looking, it may be time to run the numbers.

episodes.title: Episode 43: How To Fund Your Startup Idea
episodes.author: Jean Chatzky
episodes.summary: Do you feel like your business idea is an impossible dream? It doesn't have to be.

episodes.title: Episode 42: The Future Of Work
episodes.author: Jean Chatzky
episodes.summary: Is your job "have laptop, will travel"? Or more "Home Alone"? Or are you still part of the 9-to-6 (and counting) workforce and are looking for solutions to give you more of a life?

episodes.title: Episode 41: Life Happens! You’ve Got Questions, We’ve Got Answers
episodes.author: Jean Chatzky
episodes.summary: I believe people seek financial advice when something major happens in their lives: a marriage, a divorce, a new baby, a new job, a job loss or a death in the family. That's why Kelly and I decided to dedicate another episode of HerMoney to your most pressing questions.

episodes.title: Episode 40: Is Work-Life Balance Possible? Get Rid Of The Guilt, For Good
episodes.author: Jean Chatzky
episodes.summary: Work-life wellness expert Samantha Ettus says the answer to that question is yes.

episodes.title: Episode 39: New Year, New (Richer) You
episodes.author: Jean Chatzky
episodes.summary: We were looking for a little kick in the financial butt to get us off to a smashing start in 2017 — so we invited Tiffany Aliche (rhymes with ceviche), "The Budgetnista," to make a house call.

episodes.title: Episode 38: Your New Year’s Resolution: Granted
episodes.author: Jean Chatzky
episodes.summary: A perennial on the list of the top New Year's Resolutions: "Spend less, save more."

episodes.title: Episode 37: The She-Wolves Of Wall Street
episodes.author: Jean Chatzky
episodes.summary: It's science: Women are better investors than men.

episodes.title: Episode 36: Get Present Over Perfect With Shauna Niequist
episodes.author: Jean Chatzky
episodes.summary: Are you feeling frantic this holiday season? How about on a daily basis?

episodes.title: Episode 35: Millennial Money 101
episodes.author: Jean Chatzky
episodes.summary: There's no disputing that millennials have had it rough — taking it all in as their parents stressed through the recession and graduating college in a lousy job market with a mountain of student loan debt. But that was yesterday.

episodes.title: Episode 34: How To Pay For College Without Going Broke
episodes.author: Jean Chatzky
episodes.summary: The earlier release of the FAFSA (Free Application For Federal Student Aid) this year has brought on a lot of confusion and stress. We're here to help.

episodes.title: Episode 33: When Is A Sale Not Really A Sale? And Other Truths You Need This Shopping Season
episodes.author: Jean Chatzky
episodes.summary: Before you start shopping this holiday season, this episode is full of tips and tricks you need.

episodes.title: Episode 32: How A Shark Got Her Fins
episodes.author: Jean Chatzky
episodes.summary: You may know that Barbara Corcoran, real estate mogul and ABC "Shark Tank" investor, parlayed a $1,000 loan from a friend into a $5 billion empire. But how about the fact that in order to triumph, she — like so many of us — needed to declare war on the negative voice inside her head.

episodes.title: Episode 31: Get Paid More (For Doing What You Love)
episodes.author: Jean Chatzky
episodes.summary: Are you happy with your job? Or do you feel like you're wasting time in the wrong career — but don't know what your next move would be anyway?

episodes.title: Episode 30: The Power Of Positivity
episodes.author: Jean Chatzky
episodes.summary: Would you believe me if I told you that you could jet around the world in six-figure style for only $300? We'll teach you how your credit card points and airline miles can make it possible for you.

episodes.title: Episode 29: Work Because You Want To, Not Because You Have To
episodes.author: Jean Chatzky
episodes.summary: Work because you want to, not because you have to. How good does that sound? Radio host, columnist and my friend Clark Howard knows more about how to save money than anyone I know.

episodes.title: Episode 28: Call Your Girlfriends!
episodes.author: Jean Chatzky
episodes.summary: What's it like to be in business with your best friend? Ann Friedman, co-host of the hot podcast for besties everywhere, Call Your Girlfriend, joins us for some no-holds-barred conversation on this week's episode of HerMoney.

episodes.title: Episode 27: Oh, Grow Up!
episodes.author: Jean Chatzky
episodes.summary: Do you make your financial decisions based on fear? Stress? Guilt? Impulse? Or some all-too-random combination of the above? We dive into a better way to go about it.

episodes.title: Episode 26: LIVE From FinCon, Where Money Nerds Unite
episodes.author: Jean Chatzky
episodes.summary: HerMoney recently took a road trip to San Diego, California, to record a LIVE episode from FinCon, the world's largest financial content expo.

episodes.title: Episode 25: House Beautiful Or Money Pit?
episodes.author: Jean Chatzky
episodes.summary: We invited Angie Hicks, founder of Angie's List, to drop by.

episodes.title: Episode 24: Time Is Money. Productivity Expert Laura Vanderkam Teaches Us How To Get More Of Both
episodes.author: Jean Chatzky
episodes.summary: 168 hours. That's how many each of us have in a single week.

episodes.title: Episode 23: Share The Wealth
episodes.author: Jean Chatzky
episodes.summary: Would you tell a friend what you get paid? Would you do it if you knew it would help her get paid fairly?

episodes.title: Episode 22: You’ve Got Questions, We’ve Got Answers
episodes.author: Jean Chatzky
episodes.summary: Your questions have been rolling in over Twitter, Facebook and email. And so this week we decided to devote the entire episode to answering them.

episodes.title: Episode 21: Health, Wealth And Self
episodes.author: Jean Chatzky
episodes.summary: If you want the next half of your life to be just as good as the first, then you've got to get a grip on these three things, says Jo Ann Jenkins, the new CEO of AARP.

episodes.title: Episode 20: High Risk, High Reward! theSkimm Founders Share Their Story And Goal Of Empowering Millennial Women
episodes.author: Jean Chatzky
episodes.summary: Confession: Carly Zakin and Danielle Weisberg started theSkimm — the daily email newsletter you, I, and 3.5 million other readers start their morning with — by floating it on their credit cards.

episodes.title: Episode 19: Randi Zuckerberg On Using Tech To Simplify Your Life — Financial And Otherwise
episodes.author: Jean Chatzky
episodes.summary: As my listeners know, I'm good with money. Tech? Not so much. But after interviewing technology and social media expert Randi Zuckerberg, I feel much better. And I think you will, too.

episodes.title: Episode 18: What’s A Want Versus A Need? Sarah Newcomb Answers The Loaded Question
episodes.author: Jean Chatzky
episodes.summary: A bubble bath, a nice scotch and some slow jazz? Which are wants? Which are needs? I thought I knew until I sat down with behavioral economist Sarah Newcomb for this week's episode of HerMoney.

episodes.title: Episode 17: Brené Brown Makes Sense Of Why Money Makes Us Feel So Vulnerable — And How To Deal
episodes.author: Jean Chatzky
episodes.summary: To paraphrase Sara Bareilles: We want to see you be brave managing your money. And who better to inspire us to get there than best-selling author and preeminent TED talker Dr. Brené Brown?

episodes.title: Episode 16: Live Longer, Live Younger! Your Best Age Is Now With Dr. Robi Ludwig
episodes.author: Jean Chatzky
episodes.summary: No more midlife crises! Tired of all the negative talk surrounding the word "midlife"? So was my friend and psychotherapist Dr. Robi Ludwig — so much so, she wrote a book about it: "Your Best Age Is Now."

episodes.title: Episode 15: How To Put $500 A Month Back In Your Pocket And Jump-Start Your Savings Plan!
episodes.author: Jean Chatzky
episodes.summary: How To Put $500 A Month Back In Your Pocket And Jump-Start Your Savings Plan! When To Save Vs. When To Splurge. Plus, Learn How To Start Tracking Those Savings. It's addictive!

episodes.title: Episode 14: It’s All About Me! How To Take Credit — Without Being Called A B****. Plus Actress Ali Sweeney On ID Theft!
episodes.author: Jean Chatzky
episodes.summary: How can women learn to be more assertive at work and at home without being called bitchy? Dr. Ben Sorensen, a charismatic leadership trainer and executive coach, knows how.

episodes.title: Episode 13: Jane Bryant Quinn On How To Make Your Money Last As Long As You DO!
episodes.author: Jean Chatzky
episodes.summary: I am so proud to call Jane Bryant Quinn a friend as well as a mentor. You know her as a female pioneer and personal finance advocate, trusted by millions as a columnist for Newsweek, a reporter for CBS News and a prolific author, but to me, she is an inspiration. Jane showed me –– and so many others –– there was a space in the world for women to talk in a smart, intelligent and understandable way about money.

episodes.title: Episode 12: You Don’t Have To Be Perfect, Just Good Enough With Rene Syler
episodes.author: Jean Chatzky
episodes.summary: "I lost my job, I lost my breasts, I lost my hair and I found myself." That's Rene Syler, former anchor for CBS News' The Early Show, on HerMoney explaining what happened in a tumultuous two years of her life.

episodes.title: Episode 11: When A Spender And A Saver Say ‘I Do,’ How Do They Manage The Money? A Candid Chat With Author Jennifer Weiner
episodes.author: Jean Chatzky
episodes.summary: Candid. If I had to pick one word to describe Jennifer Weiner, author of "Good in Bed," "In Her Shoes" and so many other great reads, I'd pick that one. Though, smart, funny and fearless also come to mind. I knew I wanted her on the podcast the minute I read her frank essay about the fact that she and her new husband are polar opposites financially.

episodes.title: Episode 10: Will The 50-Year-Old You Be Mad At The 25-Year-Old You? Talking Time-Tested Money Principles With Dave Ramsey
episodes.author: Jean Chatzky
episodes.summary: Dave Ramsey asks, "Will The 50-Year-Old You Be Mad At The 25-Year-Old You?" This week I traveled to Nashville to sit down with financial powerhouse Dave Ramsey and his daughter Rachel Cruze. We talk about how the baby steps to take control of our own financial lives haven't changed in the 25 years Dave and I have been doing this – and how they have.

episodes.title: Episode 9: How I Found $1,000 And Learned About Grit From Ad Aces Linda Kaplan Thaler And Robin Koval
episodes.author: Jean Chatzky
episodes.summary: Grit – and a grand! In this episode of HerMoney, I fill you in on how I found over $1,000 in missing money (my own, embarrassingly) and how you can do the same. And, I get the down and dirty on GRIT and how the power of Guts, Resilience, Initiative and Tenacity can take you from ordinary to extraordinary.

episodes.title: Episode 8: Your Money, Your Kids. The Opposite Of Spoiled With Ron Lieber
episodes.author: Jean Chatzky
episodes.summary: Tell your children how much money you make! That’s what Ron Lieber, NYT best-selling author, personal finance columnist and father says to do if you want to raise kids who are grounded, giving and yes, smart, about money.

episodes.title: Episode 7: Slim Body, Fat Wallet: America’s Toughest Trainer, Jillian Michaels, On Habits That Breed Success In Both
episodes.author: Jean Chatzky
episodes.summary: We all know Jillian Michaels is an expert at getting people motivated to change their lives, but she struggles with a work/home balance just like the rest of us. Jill admits money is an uncomfortable topic for her, but she sees psychological parallels in building strong fitness and financial habits.

episodes.title: Episode 6: Giada De Laurentiis On Building A Brand – And Being Heard And Respected In A Male-Dominated Industry
episodes.author: Jean Chatzky
episodes.summary: This week on HerMoney: Building your brand, honing your credit and Giada De Laurentiis. The Food Network star and restaurateur talks candidly about rising to the top in the male-dominated food world and how hard it’s been to be both heard and respected.

episodes.title: Episode 5: Joanna Coles, Editor-In-Chief Of Cosmopolitan Magazine On Sex, Money And Power
episodes.author: Jean Chatzky
episodes.summary: Sex. Money. Power. Joanna Coles, the editor-in-chief of Cosmopolitan, is very much in tune with the voice of her magazine. She is comfortable talking about anything. And this week nothing is off the table.

episodes.title: Episode 4: All-Star Investor Karen Finerman On The Costly Money Mistakes Many Women Are Making – And How Multitasking Is A Huge Waste Of Time
episodes.author: Jean Chatzky
episodes.summary: All-Star Investor Karen Finerman On The Costly Money Mistakes Many Women Are Making – And How Multitasking Is A Huge Waste Of Time

episodes.title: Episode 3: Eyes Wide Shut! Arianna Huffington Teaches Us How To Sleep Our Way To Success
episodes.author: Jean Chatzky
episodes.summary: Eyes Wide Shut! Arianna Huffington Teaches Us How To Sleep Our Way To Success.

episodes.title: Episode 2: Co-Creators Of Criminal, Phoebe Judge and Lauren Spohrer, On Turning A Passion Into A Business
episodes.author: Jean Chatzky
episodes.summary: How To Turn A Passion Into A Business. (A Behind-The-Scenes Look At The Hit Podcast Criminal!)

episodes.title: Episode 1: Gretchen Rubin On Money And Happiness
episodes.author: Jean Chatzky
episodes.summary: Can Money Buy You Happiness? Yes! And: No. Easy habits to get yourself on a happier track.

episodes.title: Welcome
episodes.author: Jean Chatzky
episodes.summary: Personal Finance Expert. Award-Winning Journalist. Best-Selling Author.
